I"^<h2 id="elevator-pitch">Elevator Pitch</h2>

<p>Transpile source code into other source code.</p>

<h2 id="synopsis">Synopsis</h2>

<p>Transpile source code into other source code.</p>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">Prep</code> works on blocks of text bracketed by REGEXPs, using PEG to transpile the blocks.</p>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">Prep</code> is like <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">sed</code> but uses grammars instead of REGEX and uses <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">glue</code> instead of REGEX rewriting syntax.</p>

<h2 id="youtube">Youtube</h2>

<p><a href="https://guitarvydas.github.io/2022/01/20/PREP-Tool.html">Prep</a></p>

<h2 id="github">Github</h2>

<p>https://github.com/guitarvydas/prep</p>

<p>See the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">doc/</code> and <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">presentation/</code> subdirectories.  Most of the documentation has been done in markdown using Obsidian.</p>

<h2 id="usage">Usage</h2>

<p>I think that all you need is to have <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">prep</code> (a JS shebang script) on your path.</p>

<p>You need to <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">npm</code> install <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">Ohm-JS</code>, <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">atob</code>, <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">pako</code>, <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">yargs</code>. [I’ve probably missed some items - let me know].</p>

